page.title: 01GENERAL REVIEW
page.content: The area is mostly of a farming narure. he ground is undulating. It is mostly arable. In the north west corner is the village. In the south east corner is the Beacon house and Round house. As you approach the village trees make their appearance and gradually the houses start to emerge. The Devils Dyke is at the north east corner. At the south west corner is Swaffam Bulbeck. The farms are mostly along Heath Road, Swaffam Prior. The others are between this road and Heath Road, Swaffam Bulbeck. Middle Hill is a hill between the two roads which reaches up to 125 feet above sea level. This is two feet off the highest level in the area. It is a quite chalky area.
